# Writing Systems Project

This is a comprehensive writing systems database built with Nuxt 3, Prisma, and PostgreSQL.

## Project Structure

```
writing-systems/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ prisma/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ schema.prisma          # Database schema with Language, Script, Country, Character models
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ seed.ts                # Seed data for initial database population
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ server/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ api/
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ languages/         # CRUD endpoints for languages
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ scripts/           # CRUD endpoints for scripts
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ countries/         # CRUD endpoints for countries
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ characters/        # CRUD endpoints for characters
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queries/           # Complex query endpoints
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ relations/         # Junction table management endpoints
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ utils/
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ prisma.ts          # Prisma client singleton
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ docker-compose.yml         # PostgreSQL database container
в””в”Ђв”Ђ nuxt.config.ts            # Nuxt configuration
```

## Database Models

### Core Models
- **Language**: Languages with ISO codes, families, branches, and speaker counts
- **Script**: Writing systems with ISO 15924 codes, types (alphabet, abjad, etc.), and direction
- **Country**: Countries with ISO 3166 codes, regions, and populations
- **Character**: Individual Unicode characters with metadata

### Junction Tables
- **LanguageScript**: Many-to-many relationship between languages and scripts
- **LanguageCountry**: Many-to-many relationship between languages and countries

## API Routes

### CRUD Operations
All models support standard CRUD operations:
- GET `/api/{model}` - List all (with filtering)
- GET `/api/{model}/{id}` - Get single item
- POST `/api/{model}` - Create new item
- PUT `/api/{model}/{id}` - Update item
- DELETE `/api/{model}/{id}` - Delete item

### Complex Queries
- GET `/api/queries/languages-by-script` - Find languages that use a specific script
- GET `/api/queries/scripts-by-language` - Find scripts used by a language
- GET `/api/queries/countries-by-language` - Find countries where a language is spoken
- GET `/api/queries/languages-by-country` - Find languages spoken in a country
- GET `/api/queries/language-families` - Group languages by family
- GET `/api/queries/script-types` - Group scripts by type

### Relations Management
- POST `/api/relations/language-script` - Link language to script
- DELETE `/api/relations/language-script/{id}` - Remove link
- POST `/api/relations/language-country` - Link language to country
- DELETE `/api/relations/language-country/{id}` - Remove link

## Common Development Tasks

### Start Development Server
```bash
npm run dev
```

### Database Operations
```bash
npm run db:push      # Push schema changes to database
npm run db:migrate   # Create and run migrations
npm run db:seed      # Populate database with seed data
npm run db:studio    # Open Prisma Studio GUI
npm run db:reset     # Reset database and re-seed
```

### Docker Commands
```bash
docker-compose up -d    # Start PostgreSQL
docker-compose down     # Stop PostgreSQL
docker-compose logs     # View logs
```

## Example API Calls

### Get all languages with their scripts
```
GET /api/languages?include=scripts
```

### Get languages in the Indo-European family
```
GET /api/languages?family=Indo-European
```

### Get scripts used by Japanese
```
GET /api/queries/scripts-by-language?languageName=Japanese
```

### Get all alphabet-type scripts
```
GET /api/scripts?type=alphabet
```

### Get languages spoken in India
```
GET /api/queries/languages-by-country?iso3166_1=IN
```

## CSS Architecture
- Layer order: `reset в†’ base в†’ utilities`
- Component-specific styles live in `<style scoped>` inside each `.vue` file
- Only globally reusable classes (.btn, .sr-only, .error, .loading, .info) go in `utilities.css`
- CSS custom properties are declared in `:root` inside `base.css`

## Code Style
- Language: TypeScript strict
- Formatter & Linter: Biome
- All identifiers/comments: English
- Boolean state: `is*` prefix
- Event handlers: `on*` prefix
- Functions: verb-first names
- Vue templates: props always in camelCase (`:fontFamily`, not `:font-family`)